Huddle together people. It's time for some brainstorming. Spacedaily has decided to host public discussion on the nuclear initiative. This is what we have been itching for. We've had a few skirmishes with GN in the past but this will be open debate viewed by thousands of readers. We formed this movement to try and influence public opinion because we knew it would be central to the future success or failure of nuclear space systems. We now have the limelight. Simon Mansfield has given us an opportunity to exchange opinions with our opposition over a major Space news website by use of opinion articles. I wrote a report on Prometheus. Bruce has now replied with his own. I am granting Simon permission to use my latest story but we should work on something addressing Gnaw n' Pis directly.<br>
